In [packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts) I fixed a real gap in the refactor: account-scoped `SyncNode` now hydrates existing sessions on connect, parses `/v1/sessions` metadata into real `SessionInfo`, and validates server/socket payloads with Zod before mutating state. `new-session` and `update-session` events no longer create blank placeholder sessions. In [packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts) I added coverage for cold-start session hydration and real-time session discovery with metadata. In [packages/happy-sync/package.json](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/package.json) I split the test entry points so `test` runs Level 0 + Level 1, and Level 2 stays explicit under `test:e2e`.

